==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Beverage
<hw>Bev"er*age</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>bevrage</ets>, F. <ets>breuvage</ets>, fr. <ets>beivre</ets> to
drink, fr. L. <ets>bibere</ets>. Cf. <er>Bib</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>,
<er>Poison</er>, <er>Potable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Liquid for
drinking; drink; -- usually applied to drink artificially prepared and
of an agreeable flavor; <as>as, an intoxicating
<ex>beverage</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He knew no <qex>beverage</qex> but the flowing stream.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically, a name applied to various kinds of
drink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A treat, or drink money.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bevile</ent>⟦br⟧
